Request Fulfillment Process
   Description
      + Request Fulfillment (RF) handles all orders from users
       and executes Standard Changes
      Users may contact RF to discuss possible orders
   Input
      Orders from users via Service Desk
   Output
      Efficient delivery of orders
   Metrics
      Sum of time lapsed on open requests
      Response time (target < 2 hours)
   Owner: Service Operations Manager
   Process
      T: Receive Service Request from User via Service Desk
      [? Not valid according to SLA]
         Escalate to <Demand Management>; SKIP
      T: Take ticket
      T: Ensure all needs are documented
      T: Give time estimate to User
      [? Standard Change (SC)] T: Apply Standard Change
      [? RfC not needed] T: Effectuate request
         [? Request is not an SC] <Notification>
      T: Create RfC
      T: Send RfC to <Change Management>
      T: Receive communication about the RfC
         T: Forward information to User
      Notification
         T: Give final notification of result to User
